description:
Inject AST-based codebase structure into PM agent memory blocks using existing CodePerceptionWatcher data.

## Implementation
1. AST summary generator in CodePerceptionWatcher - generate structure breakdown from ASTCache
2. Health metrics section (sync status, errors_24h, graphiti_connected)
3. LettaService method to update PM agent's codebase_ast block
4. Wire into sync cycle with throttling (15min min, 1h max, trigger on ≥5 files/≥10 functions/error)

## Schema
```json
{
  "updated": "2026-01-28 06:25",
  "summary": { "files": 478, "functions": 2241 },
  "health": {
    "last_sync": "2026-01-28 06:25",
    "sync_status": "green",
    "errors_24h": 3,
    "graphiti_connected": true
  },
  "structure": {
    "lib/": { "files": 28, "functions": 173, "key_modules": ["SyncOrchestrator", "HulyService"] }
  },
  "recent_changes": [
    { "file": "lib/CodePerceptionWatcher.js", "change": "modified", "functions_delta": "+2", "when": "2h ago" }
  ]
}
```

## Benefit
Reuses existing infrastructure instead of building new endpoints. PM agents gain structural awareness of their codebase.
